1
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,700
I don't know why
this happened to us.

2
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:19,667
I think Amanda cursed you.

3
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:21,967
Can you imagine?
She sent you a dead fetus.

4
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,233
Come on.

5
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:26,100
Who in the right mind will think
of something like that?

6
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:28,900
I wonder if God
is punishing me.

7
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:31,333
God didn't want this
to happen to us.

8
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,700
Your mom did.

9
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,800
Your mom wanted this to happen.

10
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:36,633
She's the one to blame.

11
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,500
What matters is that
we're still here.

12
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:39,567
We're together.

13
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:41,367
And we love each other.

14
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:43,367
I lost a child too.

15
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,300
But I can't accept the fact

16
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:48,067
that only one person did this
to both of us.

17
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,033
It's Amanda.

18
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:53,133
I want Amanda to pay for this.

19
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,433
If it's up to me,
she needs to go back to jail.

20
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,400
Serves her right!

21
00:00:55,467 --> 00:00:56,633
She has to!

22
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:59,133
She has committed many sins
against our family.

23
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,333
Auntie...

24
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,400
What? Eden? Are you going
to defend your mom again?

25
00:01:03,467 --> 00:01:04,567
She doesn't love you!

26
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:08,467
Does this mean their wedding
is already off?

27
00:01:08,567 --> 00:01:10,667
Because that's
the only reason why

28
00:01:10,733 --> 00:01:12,733
they want to get married
in the first place, right?

29
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:16,167
If it's up to me,
the wedding is off.

30
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:18,533
It means that Red
is still single.

31
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,900
Do your best.

32
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:22,733
A pretty woman is no match
to a flirt.

33
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,833
I know, Auntie. Cheers!

34
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,100
It's a new investment scheme.

35
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:29,233
And I talked to the business
owner earlier.

36
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:31,100
Mr. Lucho Madrigal.

37
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:33,200
Are these people new in town?

38
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,167
Because they told me earlier

39
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:41,200
that a Mrs. Madrigal bought all
the bags I wanted to purchase.

40
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:41,933
Wow.

41
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:46,367
Mr. Lee, meet my wife,
Mrs. Madrigal.

42
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:49,633
Excuse me?
Do you know Mrs. Madrigal?

43
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:50,500
That's her.

44
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:54,733
Thank you.
Thank you!

45
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:58,400
Mrs. Madrigal?

46
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,700
I am...

47
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:18,967
Mrs. Madrigal!

48
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:37,333
There is something very familiar
about that Mrs. Madrigal.

49
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,067
It's like I've met her
somewhere, you know?

50
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:47,700
Maybe mutual friends?

51
00:02:49,133 --> 00:02:49,833
I don't know.

52
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:55,667
I even checked the photos,
but I didn't find her.

53
00:02:57,667 --> 00:02:59,067
Wow, Rina.

54
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:01,833
You are obsessed
with Mrs. Madrigal.

55
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:04,733
You've been talking a lot
about her lately.

56
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:09,700
Is she your new obsession
after Amanda?

57
00:03:11,467 --> 00:03:12,233
Oh my God!

58
00:03:13,633 --> 00:03:18,100
Amanda is trash compared
to Mrs. Madrigal.

59
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:20,333
And why even bring her up?

60
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,400
She's been gone for a long time.

61
00:03:23,533 --> 00:03:28,967
Rina, aren't you just insecure
because she's a competition?

62
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:34,667
I'm not insecure
with Mrs. Madrigal.

63
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,100
And she's no competition
whatsoever.

64
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:47,167
On the contrary, because we have
so many similarities...

65
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:53,300
I think she can be
my close friend

66
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:55,033
once I get the chance
to meet her.

67
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:58,400
I'd like that.

68
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:01,567
Good luck with that.

69
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,933
Rina was chasing me all the way
outside of the boutique.

70
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,400
She was so desperate.

71
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:17,033
She really wanted to know
who Mrs. Madrigal was.

72
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:21,700
Are you sure she didn't
recognize you as Amanda?

73
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:22,367
No.

74
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:23,700
It's impossible.

75
00:04:23,767 --> 00:04:28,300
I was wearing sunglasses, and
I didn't look at her directly.

76
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:31,033
And I left before
she recognized me.

77
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:33,933
Well...

78
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:40,667
you are so far off the Amanda
that she tortured.

79
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:43,733
That's why she can't connect you
to Mrs. Madrigal.

80
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,733
It's better that way.

81
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,600
It's not the right time
for her to know the truth.

82
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:51,867
We'll let her get curious
about Mrs. Madrigal.

83
00:04:52,767 --> 00:04:57,333
I can't wait for her to find out
who Mrs. Madrigal is.

84
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:00,800
She'll lose her mind.

85
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,467
Very good, Amanda.

86
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:05,333
You are now stronger, tougher...

87
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:09,933
since you put aside the sadness
because of your daughter.

88
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,333
It will only become a weakness.

89
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:15,733
And there's no room for weakness
when you want revenge.

90
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,267
Come on, you need this.

91
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,900
You need to get out.
You need fresh air, okay?

92
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,533
Red, I don't want to.

93
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,333
- You'll just stay here.
- I don't want to go out.

94
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,300
Yen, come on.

95
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:35,567
- You need this.
- I don't want to go out.

96
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:37,567
I want to stay here.
I don't want to go outside.

97
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:39,467
You need this, okay?

98
00:05:39,533 --> 00:05:42,167
You don't believe that
our baby is still alive?

99
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,400
Why don't you believe me?

100
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:50,733
I heard her cry, Red.
Why don't you believe me?

101
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:53,233
Yen...

102
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:56,167
I believe you, okay?

103
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:59,433
I believe that it's hard
for you to take.

104
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:02,733
But, Yen...

105
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:05,733
it's hard for me too.

106
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:08,433
Because...

107
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:11,033
I lost a baby too.

108
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:15,233
I lost a child too.

109
00:06:18,633 --> 00:06:20,667
I want to see our baby.

110
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:25,600
I want to see our baby,
Red, please.

111
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:28,733
Please, Red.

112
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:33,100
Yen, I have dreams
for our baby too.

113
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,133
I want to hold her.

114
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:39,667
I want to carry her.

115
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:45,400
I want to hear her laugh.

116
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,133
Yen...

117
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:52,600
I want to hear her cry.

118
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:01,100
I want to teach her
how to play football.

119
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:03,967
I can already imagine
cheering for her.

120
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:07,600
I want to see her swimming.

121
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:13,767
Yen, I want to take care of her.
I really do.

122
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:16,767
You and the baby, Yen.

123
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,833
I want to take care
of you and the baby.

124
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:22,433
I want to love you.

125
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,367
But I wasn't able to do that

126
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:29,500
because I wasn't able
to save her.

127
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,567
I couldn't do anything, Yen.
I didn't get to do anything.

128
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:49,567
Yen, it's all my fault.

129
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:54,767
I didn't get to save our baby.
It's all my fault, Yen.

130
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,600
I couldn't save our baby.

131
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:02,133
Yen, I'm sorry.

132
00:08:04,667 --> 00:08:05,433
I'm sorry.

133
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:12,400
I'm sorry, Yen.
I didn't get to save her.

134
00:08:12,467 --> 00:08:13,667
I wasn't able to do anything.

135
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,333
Sorry, I couldn't do anything.

136
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:19,933
I couldn't save her.
I'm worthless.

137
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:23,333
Sorry.

138
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:26,000
It's not our fault.

139
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,100
We didn't do anything wrong,
Red.

140
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:30,700
I didn't get to save our baby,
Yen.

141
00:08:30,767 --> 00:08:32,967
It's not our fault.

142
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,967
I'll go home now.

143
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:42,433
Good luck with your meeting.

144
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,167
Okay, take care.

145
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,867
He might see you.

146
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:28,133
Victor Ramos.

147
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:29,833
Mr. Madrigal.

148
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:32,700
I'm sorry, my wife
was in a hurry.

149
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,533
- So that was Mrs. Madrigal?
- Yes, let's go inside.

150
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,033
Okay.

151
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,533
I can't bear this anymore!

152
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,900
Please, stop!

153
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,367
I can't bear this anymore.
Stop! I'll pay you what I owe!

154
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,467
Now you know how
I collect my money.

155
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:04,400
Make sure you'll pay me.

156
00:10:04,467 --> 00:10:06,200
I'll make your family pay
if you don't keep your word.

157
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:07,900
Do you understand?

158
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,000
You're lucky I'm a good guy.
'Cause I still pity you.

159
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:27,333
My husband says he'll eat out.

160
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:32,967
He has a business meeting
tonight with Mr. Madrigal.

161
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:34,867
See, I told you.

162
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:38,133
That's why I want
to be their friend.

163
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,300
They are filthy rich.

164
00:10:41,367 --> 00:10:44,933
We can use them in our business.

165
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:50,167
I don't think Mrs. Madrigal
wants to be friends with you.

166
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,133
Didn't she walk away from you

167
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,600
when you tried
to chase her down?

168
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:54,167
She was busy at that time.

169
00:10:55,667 --> 00:10:59,000
I'm going to use a new tactic.

170
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:03,167
She will pay attention to me.

171
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:05,433
We have the same taste.

172
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:12,233
And there is this limited
edition hat that I want to buy.

173
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:15,700
I will beat her to it this time.

174
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:20,533
So make sure you collect money
from her.

175
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:23,867
I need cash because I maxed out
my credit cards already.

176
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:27,533
I want to walk into that shop
and pay in cash.

177
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:32,033
Rina, you saw what I did to her,
right?

178
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,600
She almost died.

179
00:11:34,533 --> 00:11:36,300
But, fine, I'll take care of it.

180
00:11:36,367 --> 00:11:37,633
So you can buy
whatever you want.

181
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:39,767
And one more thing.

182
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:44,333
You better not tell
Victor about this.

183
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:49,167
Victor can't find out what
I'm doing with my money.

184
00:11:49,233 --> 00:11:52,400
He might start becoming nosy
and check on my finances!

185
00:11:52,467 --> 00:11:53,700
I don't ever want
that to happen.

186
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:54,333
Yes, Rina.
I don't want him to know

187
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:58,067
what I'm doing with my money,
understood?

188
00:11:58,133 --> 00:11:59,033
Yes, Rina.
Okay, fine.

189
00:12:01,567 --> 00:12:03,100
Clean this up.

190
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,300
Are you okay?

191
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:11,667
You seem on edge.

192
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:12,967
Don't worry.

193
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:17,333
I'm not like some creditors
who are violent.

194
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,700
And I won't invite you out
to this place

195
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:25,767
if I have bad intentions.

196
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,200
Don't be scared, Victor.

197
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:33,767
It's not what I'm thinking,
Mr. Mad...

198
00:12:34,933 --> 00:12:35,700
Lucho.

199
00:12:37,967 --> 00:12:38,733
Honestly...

200
00:12:40,167 --> 00:12:42,900
no one knows that I have
financial problems.

201
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:50,333
I even lied to my wife.

202
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:54,000
I told her,
we're business partners.

203
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,133
But the truth is...

204
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,833
we're bankrupt.

205
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:03,100
That's why I need a loan
to keep my bank afloat.

206
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:05,167
And avoid getting in trouble
with my clients.

207
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:10,567
I lost their money
to a bad investment.

208
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:15,733
You must think I'm really weak,
but I just got unlucky.

209
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:16,600
And don't worry.

210
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,100
I won't run with your money.

211
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:22,967
I will pay you back with
interest like we agreed on.

212
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:25,767
I believe you.

213
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:27,933
Don't worry.

214
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:30,500
No one else will
know about this.

215
00:13:32,167 --> 00:13:32,867
Thank you.

216
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:38,333
My family's been going
through a lot right now.

217
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,033
I don't want them to worry
about our business.

218
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,700
I'm glad you came to me.

219
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:53,367
I treat my clients as friends.

220
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:56,900
So, I'll take care of you.

221
00:13:58,367 --> 00:13:59,333
Cheers.

222
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,400
Looks like the Ramoses are going
through a rough patch.

223
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,500
Victor didn't open up
about their problems.

224
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,100
I didn't try to get
more information

225
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:26,500
because he might notice
my interest.

226
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:29,167
But I can feel that he's
been going through a lot.

227
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:32,567
He's having a hard time.
He's desperate.

228
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,333
So...

229
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,967
if they're having
money problems,

230
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:43,400
I think it will be easier for
you to get your revenge, Amanda.

231
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:46,200
I kind of feel bad for him.

232
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,700
He seems like a decent guy.

233
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,233
Too bad...

234
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:53,467
he married a demon.

235
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:56,500
And Rina's wickedness
rubbed off on him.

236
00:14:56,567 --> 00:15:01,000
That's why all of them will pay
for what they did to me.

237
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:05,300
And Rina said something
that I couldn't forget.

238
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:10,400
She said I could never exact
revenge because I'm poor.

239
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:13,933
Money is everything to them.

240
00:15:15,133 --> 00:15:16,300
So this is good.

241
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:23,900
We will target them financially,
to make sure they'll suffer.

242
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:29,467
Our plans for Rina are all set.

243
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:36,700
I'm sure she'll be shocked when
she sees your surprise for her.

244
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:39,200
I'm excited.

245
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:44,167
Close your eyes. No peeking.

246
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:47,333
Red, I want to stay in my room.
I don't want to go out.

247
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:51,400
This is good for you.
You need to get some sun.

248
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:52,633
Don't worry. We're almost there.

249
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:56,600
Few more steps,
and stop.

250
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:59,067
Surprise!

251
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:04,500
You don't need to do this.

252
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:09,833
Yen...

253
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,100
I miss you.

254
00:16:13,433 --> 00:16:15,000
I miss our life on the island.

255
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,533
At least we can come here
and reminisce.

256
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:22,600
Of course, with upgraded food.

257
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:25,767
We can just come here
and talk all day.

258
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:27,833
We can stay overnight
in this tent.

259
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,400
As if we're having a honeymoon.

260
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:32,000
Quality time?

261
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:32,767
Honeymoon?

262
00:16:34,267 --> 00:16:35,933
Red, can you hear yourself?

263
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:40,033
Our baby just died and now
you want to celebrate?

264
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,200
I don't want this!

265
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:46,333
I want our baby back!

266
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,467
I thought you were
miserable too.

267
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:52,900
I thought you were grieving.

268
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:55,567
But why do you want to
forget about my baby?

269
00:16:58,400 --> 00:16:59,600
Yen, that's not what I meant.

270
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:00,933
What is it, then?

271
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,500
Don't you want to be in
this situation anymore?

272
00:17:02,567 --> 00:17:05,567
Are you tired of it?
Is that why you want to forget?

273
00:17:05,633 --> 00:17:07,733
Yen, that's not my intention.

274
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,133
You know that.

275
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,200
You know I love our baby.

276
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:15,233
And you know I'm hurting too,
okay?

277
00:17:16,533 --> 00:17:18,333
But we have to accept
the truth...

278
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,600
that our baby's gone.

279
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:23,367
Yen, she's not coming back...

280
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,467
okay?

281
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:31,000
Now, for our baby's sake...

282
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:34,967
let her rest in peace.

283
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:35,867
We have to let her go.

284
00:17:35,933 --> 00:17:38,100
No! I will not let her go!

285
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:38,933
Yen!

286
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,800
- Our baby is not dead!
- Yen.

287
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:42,100
Yen.

288
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:45,067
Come on, Red!
Our baby is still alive!

289
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:48,333
Why don't you believe me?
She's still alive.

290
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:52,600
She's not gone. It's impossible.
I heard her.

291
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:55,267
I heard her cry, Red.
She's still alive.

292
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:58,033
She's well and alive, Red.

293
00:17:59,267 --> 00:18:01,633
Did you know that I named her?

294
00:18:03,267 --> 00:18:05,667
I named her Chloe.

295
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:10,167
Chloe's still alive, Red.

296
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:12,400
We can't let her go.

297
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:16,067
She's not gone.
It's impossible to happen.

298
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:21,633
So no matter what you do,
no matter what you say...

299
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:25,667
I won't believe you.

300
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:27,667
She's still alive.

301
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,333
I will not move on, Red.

302
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:32,533
I will not let go!

303
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,167
You're not used to
drinking that stuff.

304
00:19:00,767 --> 00:19:03,633
I just wanted to take my mind
off things, Mom.

305
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:12,467
Come here.

306
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:22,800
Did you and Eden
have a fight again?

307
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:29,433
Well, I tried to set
something up for her.

308
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:34,400
You know, to make her
forget all the pain.

309
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:38,233
Like I used to do for
you before, remember?

310
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,167
When you were grieving
about my brother's death.

311
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:43,867
And you know how much
I appreciated that.

312
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:49,267
Well, apparently, not Yenyen.

313
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:55,333
I want her to feel better...

314
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:57,333
even for just a moment.

315
00:19:59,200 --> 00:19:59,900
But...

316
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:05,200
she's accusing me of wanting
to forget our baby.

317
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,967
You have been such
a good boyfriend to Eden.

318
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:16,000
If she doesn't see that,

319
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:19,733
if she doesn't appreciate it,
it's on her.

320
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,833
I don't know, maybe...

321
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,900
she's just struggling.

322
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,133
After all, she was the one
who carried our baby.

323
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,700
Listen to you, Son.

324
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,100
You're not like this.

325
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,100
I miss that...

326
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,933
happy, jolly person
that you are.

327
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,833
Where is that Red?

328
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:55,967
You know what?

329
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:59,400
Maybe you should follow
your own advice.

330
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:02,233
Why don't you go out?

331
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,667
Go out with your friends.

332
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:07,600
What about Yenyen?

333
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:14,633
Maybe it's better
to stay this way.

334
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,867
Give her some space for now.

335
00:21:19,233 --> 00:21:22,167
Go out with your friends.
Have a few drinks. Have fun.

336
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:25,300
You deserve it.

337
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:54,667
So there's only one piece
of this hat...

338
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:56,667
in the Philippines?

339
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:58,733
Yes, Ma'am.

340
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:04,500
All right.

341
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:06,833
Consider it sold.
It's mine, then.

342
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:11,200
Don't ever give it to anyone.
Reserve it for me, please.

343
00:22:11,267 --> 00:22:12,967
But we cannot guarantee

344
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:15,533
that no one will buy this
straight away, Madame.

345
00:22:16,867 --> 00:22:17,333
But...

346
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:20,067
I'll be back this afternoon.

347
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,800
Reserve it for me.

348
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:26,300
Don't give it to Mrs. Madrigal,
okay?

349
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:32,433
Look, I know we are both patrons
here in your boutique.

350
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:36,067
But I've already spent lots
of money here in your shop.

351
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:39,467
So if you can do that for me,
I will be back this afternoon.

352
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:47,233
I will pay you in cash and throw
in a big tip for you, okay?

353
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:50,433
I'll be back this afternoon.

354
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:11,833
Yes, Rina?

355
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,733
Did you get the money?

356
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,400
Have you collected our money?

357
00:23:15,467 --> 00:23:16,567
You're so impatient.

358
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:19,800
He's on his way.
I'm waiting for him.

359
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:24,567
Make sure to get the money
because I need it.

360
00:23:24,667 --> 00:23:26,967
I am buying that hat.

361
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,633
Yes, Rina.

362
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:30,600
Okay, I'll call you back.

363
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:31,833
He'll be here in a minute.

364
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:33,300
Yes.

365
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:35,500
Thank you.

366
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:42,367
Excuse me.

367
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:58,200
Are you sure you got everything?
Remember, I know where you live.

368
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:00,000
This is my last payment.

369
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,633
So I won't mess with you
and I want this to be over.

370
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:29,667
Hello?

371
00:24:29,733 --> 00:24:30,833
Hello?

372
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:31,900
Hey, Elmer.

373
00:24:31,967 --> 00:24:33,100
Lucho.

374
00:24:33,167 --> 00:24:34,233
I did what you wanted.

375
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:35,700
Very good.

376
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:37,600
Don't be scared.

377
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,433
We'll keep our end
of the bargain.

378
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:47,133
That how's easy
she took the bait.

379
00:24:48,833 --> 00:24:51,967
She'll get the money in a while.

380
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:55,467
And I know where
she'll spend it first.

381
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,767
I know Elmer.

382
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:05,033
He can't do this alone.

383
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,733
He can't come up with this
on his own.

384
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:10,033
Get back to him.
Tell him to pay us.

385
00:25:10,867 --> 00:25:14,067
If he's working with someone
in messing with us...

386
00:25:15,067 --> 00:25:16,400
find out who it is.

387
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:20,233
We're just glad that you're here
after what happened.

388
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:21,167
Let's just have fun.

389
00:25:22,033 --> 00:25:23,467
One round of drinks on me.

390
00:25:23,533 --> 00:25:24,700
Nice!

391
00:25:24,767 --> 00:25:25,533
- Shot!
- Let's drink.

392
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,667
Emma, have you seen Red?

393
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:29,800
Why are you looking for my son?

394
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:31,267
Do you want to fight
with him again?

395
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:34,167
Red usually goes out drinking
with his friends

396
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,000
when he's in a bad mood.

397
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:37,233
Didn't you know that about him?

398
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:40,200
I was just talking to Sab.
We're just being friends.

399
00:25:40,267 --> 00:25:41,567
Is Sabina a good friend?

400
00:25:41,633 --> 00:25:42,600
Have you forgotten what
she did on the island...

401
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:44,133
That's so long ago!

402
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,067
Sab has already moved on.

403
00:25:46,133 --> 00:25:49,267
Something you're not
capable of doing.

404
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:52,133
Honestly, Yen,
Sab is better than you.

405
00:25:53,233 --> 00:25:55,567
Because she talks to me.

406
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:57,733
She listens to me...

407
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:00,367
while you don't!
